Dean and Petra Lategan&#8217;s house in Matjiesrivier.Dean Lategan, owner of a farm in Matjiesrivier close to the Swartberg Pass outside Oudtshoorn, described yesterday&#8217;s strong winds in the area as the worst ever on the farm.Roofs were blown off and trees uprooted in the area.He wrote on Facebook: &#8220;This is the worst storm I have experienced in my life on the farm. Our neighbour&#8217;s house was struck by a tree that is over 100 years old and a few hours later the other branch destroyed the power lines.Dean and his wife Petra are the owners of Latana Cheese, a business that has received many awards in recent years.